s the Chief Technology Officer and oversees all technical development.\n\nIn 2019, TechNova secured its first major funding round led by Venture Capital Partners, raising $15 million in Series A funding. The lead investor, James Park from Venture Capital Partners, joined the board of directors and has been instrumental in guiding the company\'s growth strategy. The funding enabled TechNova to expand its research and development team and establish partnerships with major healthcare institutions.\n\nThe company\'s flagship product, MedAI Platform, was launched in 2020 and quickly gained traction among hospitals and medical centers across the United States. MedAI Platform utilizes advanced machine learning algorithms to analyze medical imaging data and assist radiologists in early disease detection. The platform has been particularly successful in detecting breast cancer, lung cancer, and neurological disorders with accuracy rates exceeding 95%.\n\nDr. Emily Watson, the Chief Medical Officer who joined TechNova in 2020, previously worked as a radiologist at Johns Hopkins \n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o', 'max_tokens': 3000, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.0}}
