 regulatory requirements. Under her guidance, the platform received FDA approval in late 2020, making it one of the first AI-powered diagnostic tools to achieve this milestone.\n\nTechNova\'s engineering team is led by Alex Thompson, the Vice President of Engineering, who previously worked at Amazon Web Services for eight years. The team consists of 45 software engineers, 12 data scientists, and 8 quality assurance specialists, all working from the company\'s headquarters in Austin and a satellite office in San Francisco, California.\n\nIn 2021, TechNova formed a strategic partnership with HealthSystem Alliance, a network of over 200 hospitals across North America. This partnership allowed TechNova to deploy MedAI Platform in numerous medical facilities and gather valuable real-world performance data. The collaboration has been overseen by Lisa Martinez, TechNova\'s Vice President of Partnerships, who has extensive experience in healthcare business development.\n\nThe company\'s research division, headed by Dr. Kevin Zhang, focuses on developing next-generation AI technologies \n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o', 'max_tokens': 3000, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.0}}
